  <!-- Code Intelligence system preferences:
        "codeintel_enabled" is the master pref indicating if the Code Intel
            system is running at all. It should NOT be set on a per file or
            per project level.
        "codeintel_sort_codebrowser_by" is the sort-order to use in the
            Code Browser.
        "codeintel_completion_languages" is a space-separated list of
            languages for which Komodo considers providing CodeIntel-based
            autocomplete and calltips. This should not be overridden: this is
            basically a convenient location to hard code this data.
        "codeintel_completion_triggering_enabled"
            This indicates if completion triggers should fire automatically
            while editing. <Ctrl+J> to manually open these UIs is still
            available.
        "codeintel_rescan_while_typing_enabled" indicates if scan requests
            should be issued for the current file while it is being edited.
        "codeintel_scanning_imports_enabled" indicates whether the CodeIntel
            system should schedule (re)scans of imported modules.
        "codeintel_calltip_max_lines" the maximum number of lines to display
            onscreen when showing a calltip.
        "codeintel_calltip_max_line_width" the maximum width of individual
            calltip lines when showing a calltip.
        "codeintel_completion_fillups_enabled" indicates whether the fill-up
            functionality of AutoComplete is enabled. "Fill-up" is where
            typing a certain char (like '(' or '.') during an AutoComplete
            session will trigger insertion of the current completion *and*
            that char. This is separate from the usual insertion via <Tab>
            or <Enter>. Each language has its own appropriate set of
            completion fillups.
        "codeintel_have_preloaded_database" is a boolean indicating if
            the codeintel database has been pre-loaded for this version.
        "codeintel_selected_catalogs" is a string-repr of a list of codeintel
            catalog selections.
        "codeintel_scan_files_in_project" is a boolean indicating whether
            codeintel should scan all files and directories in the associated
            project (i.e. of the current file being edited).
        "codeintel_max_recursive_dir_depth" is an integer indicating the
            maximum number of sub-directories deep the system will look
            under configured PHP and JavaScript import dirs.
    -->
